Initial Assessment:
- Identify the device type and model
- Gather description of the issue
- Determine if issue affects one user or multiple users
- Check if device is local or network-connected

{% if device_type == 'printer' %}
Printer Troubleshooting:
- Verify printer is powered on and online
- Check for paper jams and paper tray status
- Review ink/toner levels
- Print test page from printer itself
- Check print queue for stuck jobs

Network Printer Steps:
- Verify printer network connectivity (ping test)
- Confirm printer IP address is correct
- Check print server status if applicable
- Verify user has printer mapped correctly

Driver Issues:
- Check installed driver version
- Remove and reinstall printer driver
- Download latest driver from manufacturer
- Configure correct printer settings and defaults
{% endif %}

{% if device_type == 'docking_station' %}
Docking Station Troubleshooting:
- Verify dock is receiving power
- Check USB-C/Thunderbolt connection
- Update docking station firmware
- Test with different ports on the dock
- Verify dock compatibility with laptop model
{% endif %}

{% if device_type == 'monitor' %}
Monitor Troubleshooting:
- Check power and video cable connections
- Verify correct input source selected
- Test with different cable or port
- Update display drivers
- Check display settings and resolution
{% endif %}

{% if device_type == 'scanner' %}
Scanner Troubleshooting:
- Verify scanner is powered on
- Check USB or network connection
- Install/update scanner drivers
- Test with manufacturer's scanning software
- Check for paper path obstructions
{% endif %}

Resolution:
- Document the fix applied
- Provide user guidance to prevent recurrence
- If hardware failure, initiate replacement request
- Update asset records if applicable
